This spontaneous report was received from a consumer (patient's grandmother) and concerns a 05-year-old female
patient from the United States: 017490036A.
Initial information was processed alongwith additional information received from central complaint vigilance on 23-
JAN-2016.
The patient's height and weight was not reported. The patient's medical history included hernia surgery (hernia 
removed).
The patient was treated with paracetamol (suspension, oral, batch CKB2A00, expiry 31-OCT-2014) once (2.5 
teaspoons, 1x), initiated on 21-JAN-2016 for sore throat. Concomitant medications were not reported.
