FDA - Adverse Event Reporting System (FAERS) 
FOIA Case Report Information
Preferred Term ( MedDRA  Version: 19.0 ReC
It was reported that on 21-JAN-216, the patient's grandmother gave paracetamol suspension 2.5 teaspoons to her 
granddaughter (took higher than recommended dose) which was already expired (expired product used). The 
reporter mentioned that she had arthritis in her hands, so to squeze this bottle, it was a little hard for her. It worked 
so well for the kids though and also reported that she couldn't read the expiration date that well from the box but 
could see it on the bottle (product packaging issue).
Action taken with paracetamol was not reported.
The outcome was not reported for expired product used, took higher than recommended dose and product 
packaging issue. 
This report was associated with product quality complaint and product complaint number was 10000576393.
This report was not serious.